<td valign=top>
<b class="welcome"><font color="#3366CC">About Zimbra</font></b><p>
Zimbra Collaboration Suite (ZCS) 4.0 is modern, innovative messaging and collaboration. Zimbra is the leading open source <a href="http://www.zimbra.com/products/solutions.html">solution</a> for enterprise, service provider, academic, and government environments; offering administrators and their end-users unmatched <a href="http://www.zimbra.com/products/benefits.html">benefits</a>. It's no wonder Zimbra is popular choice for today's growing Mac and Linux email server base.
<p>
<a href="http://www.zimbra.com/products/collaboration.html">Ajax based collaboration</a> is at the heart of ZCS 4.0. The powerful web client integrates email, contacts, shared calendar, VoIP, and now online document authoring and sharing. Our unique <a href="http://www.zimbra.com/products/zimlets.html">Zimlet</a> technology make it easy to include custom 'mash-ups' in ZCS.
<p>
ZCS 4.0 also features an <a href="http://www.zimbra.com/products/zimbra_admin.html">Ajax Admin Interface</a> plus full scripting tools, and support for standards-based APIs (IMAP / POP / iCal) which enable seamless compatibility with Microsoft Outlook and Apple.
<p>
Zimbra is also pleased to announce <a href="http://www.zimbra.com/products/zimbra_mobile.html">Zimbra Mobile</a>, the first integrated offering for open source with no need for third party software or additional servers for most devices.
</td>
